726916f-a.title: Queens: Hoyt Avenue - 23rd Street
726916f-a.text:
Hoyt Avenue, south side, west from 24th to 23rd Streets. In the foreground is a small sheet-metal vegetable store and the rears of several houses fronting on the east side of 23rd Street. At the S.W. corner of the latter is an old farmhouse, having been part of the Hallett property in 1873.
P. L. Sperr  March 14, 1931

725132f-a.title: Queens: 23rd Street - Hoyt Avenue
725132f-a.text:
23rd Street, south from Hoyt Avenue. The tree in the lower right hand corner shrouds from view a very old farmhouse. Above the tree apnears Public School No. 7. Some mid-Manhattan skyscrapers are in the upper right hand corner.
P. L. Sperr  July 25, 1936

726913f-b.text:

726914f-c.title: Queens: Hoyt Avenue - 23rd Street
726914f-c.text:
